
Your **NGINX** is only listening on:

listen 80;

👉 That’s **HTTP only**
👉 No HTTPS (`443`) server is configured

---

# Fix: Enable HTTPS in NGINX

## 1. Install SSL support (if not already)

sudo pacman -S openssl

---

## 2. Generate self-signed certificate (for testing)

sudo mkdir -p /etc/nginx/ssl

sudo openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 \
-newkey rsa:2048 \
-keyout /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.key \
-out /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.crt

---

## 3. Add HTTPS server block

Edit config:

sudo nano /etc/nginx/nginx.conf

Add:

server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name localhost;

    ssl_certificate     /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.crt;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.key;

    location /api {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8080;
    }
}

---

## 4. Reload NGINX

sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx

---

## 5. Test

curl -k "https://localhost/api?key=test"

👉 `-k` = ignore self-signed cert warning

---

# Optional (best practice)

Redirect HTTP → HTTPS:

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name localhost;

    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
}

---

# Key concept

* Port **80 → HTTP**
* Port **443 → HTTPS (SSL/TLS)**
* Without SSL config → HTTPS won’t work at all

